Performance Rate #-1-Patients with Type 2 Diabetes Mellitus who  experience a decrease in HgbA1C of >1% from the highest value during the measurement year OR the previous year to the most recent value .  

Performance Rate #2-Patients who  experience an increase in HgbA1C of >1% from the lowest value during the measurement year OR the previous year to the most recent value; 

Performance Rate #3-The difference between Performance Rate 1 and Performance Rate 2, divided by the total denominator.

This measure examines systolic blood pressure for patients with hypertension using 3 Performance Rates: 
Performance Rate #1-Percent of patients with diagnosis of hypertension who during the measurement year or the prior year had at least one systolic blood pressure of >160 mm. Hg AND who experience a >20 mmHg decrease from the highest value in the measurement year or prior year to the most recent value recent value;

Performance Rate # 2-Percent of patients with diagnosis of hypertension who  who during the measurement year or the prior year have at least one systolic blood pressure of < 160 mm. Hg AND who experience a >20 mmHg decrease from the highest value in the measurement year or prior year to the most recent value recent value;

Performance Rate #3- The difference between Performance Rate 1 and Performance Rate 2, divided by the total denominator.

